 {"id":"caam-62p4","title":"EPIC: Identity & JWT Extraction","description":"# EPIC: Identity & JWT Extraction

## Strategic Context

CodexBar extracts rich identity information (email, organization, plan type) from stored JWT tokens WITHOUT making API calls. This is valuable because:
1. Faster than API calls (instant, local-only)
2. Works offline
3. Provides plan type info that helps with rotation decisions (enterprise accounts may have different limits)

## Background

### Current State in caam
caam currently has no way to know:
- Which email/account a profile belongs to (unless user named it correctly)
- What subscription plan the account has (Max, Pro, Team, Enterprise)
- What organization the account belongs to (for team accounts)

### How JWT Extraction Works
OAuth tokens (especially Codex's auth.json) contain a JWT ID token. JWTs have three parts: header.payload.signature (base64 encoded). The payload contains "claims" including:
- email: The account email
- plan_type or subscription_type: "max", "pro", "team", "enterprise"
- org or organization: Organization name (team accounts)
- exp: Expiration timestamp

We can base64-decode the payload WITHOUT verifying the signature (we trust it since it came from the provider). This gives us rich identity info for free.

### Claude's Approach
Claude stores identity differently - in .credentials.json with a claudeAiOauth object that may contain:
- accountId
- subscriptionType: "max", "pro", etc.

## Technical Approach

### New Package: internal/identity/

```go
type Identity struct {
    Email        string    `json:"email,omitempty"`
    Organization string    `json:"organization,omitempty"`
    PlanType     string    `json:"plan_type,omitempty"`  // max, pro, team, enterprise
    AccountID    string    `json:"account_id,omitempty"`
    ExpiresAt    time.Time `json:"expires_at,omitempty"`
    Provider     string    `json:"provider"`
}

func ExtractFromCodexAuth(path string) (*Identity, error)
func ExtractFromClaudeCredentials(path string) (*Identity, error)
func ExtractFromGeminiSettings(path string) (*Identity, error)
```

### Integration Points
- internal/profile/profile.go: Add Identity field to Profile struct
- cmd/caam/cmd/status.go: Display identity info
- internal/rotation/rotation.go: Use plan_type in scoring (enterprise gets boost)

## Deliverables
1. JWT parser for Codex auth.json
2. Claude credentials parser for identity
3. Gemini settings parser for identity
4. Profile identity enrichment on load
5. Display identity in status/ls commands

## Success Criteria
- Extract email from 100% of valid OAuth profiles
- Extract plan type from providers that expose it
- No API calls required
- Sub-millisecond extraction time

## Dependencies
- None (foundational)

## Enables
- Better rotation scoring (plan type boost)
- User-friendly profile display
